<item>
 <title>Grape</title>
 <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/smoothiecast/~3/K2dU154KbLE/grape</link>
 <description>&lt;h3&gt;The Grape (well… Grapes, one wouldn’t be all that great)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Famous for its use in wine along with jams, pickles, jelly and it’s seeds are also used to make oil. They come in a variety of colours and flavours (Great for mixing and matching). When dried in the sun, these big juicy nuggets turn into the much loved raisin, mmmmmmmmmmm!&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;!--break--&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img src="/files/grape.jpg" alt="purple grapes" align="right" /&gt;Grapes can make microwaves go crazy and malfunction if you create a correct structure with them, how verily odd!!!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Storage&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cool place out of the sun, we like them in the fridge, they taste much better and keep longer, bargain!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Usage&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ASAP after purchase, wash before use&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Nutritional stuff&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Antioxidant, anti-histamine and anti-inflammatory (good for Jakes hay-fever), Vit C, could lower cholesterol and prevent heart disease (can’t be a bad thing)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Tips&lt;/h3&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Get seedless grapes, seeds don’t take well to smoothies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grapes can be used to naturally sweeten any smoothie of your choice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grapes can be used as ‘nice cubes’- frozen and used instead of ice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
&lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/smoothiecast?a=K2dU154KbLE:aajVRTpSPU8:yIl2AUoC8zA"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/smoothiecast?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/smoothiecast?a=K2dU154KbLE:aajVRTpSPU8:UT3xtbGYFzA"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/smoothiecast?d=UT3xtbGYFzA" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/smoothiecast?a=K2dU154KbLE:aajVRTpSPU8:o5wlBzp-bFI"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/smoothiecast?d=o5wlBzp-bFI" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</description>
 <comments>http://www.smoothiecast.co.uk/fruit+files/grape#comments</comments>
 <category domain="http://www.smoothiecast.co.uk/category/fruit+files">Fruit Files</category>
 <pubDate>Fri, 09 Feb 2007 13:34:38 -0800</pubDate>
 <dc:creator>mail@smoothiecast.co.uk (Ian Egner and Jake Mahal)</dc:creator>
 <guid isPermaLink="false">61 at http://www.smoothiecast.co.uk</guid>
