<item>
 <title>Melon, Apple and Pear</title>
 <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/smoothiecast/~3/tDjK1Qe1Qks/melon+apple+and+pear</link>
 <description>&lt;p&gt;To make this smoothie you will need:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1 Small melon or 1/2 medium melon&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 Large pears&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 Small apples&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6 Ice cubes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pinch of cinnamon (This adds a dynamic flavour and extra health benefits)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Water or juice if required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Slice up all the fruit into tiny pieces (but don't lose them) and put them in the smoothie maker. Add a pinch of cinnamon. Put the ice in. Then hit the on button and smooth away. If your smoothie maker can't whizz it all you may need to stop and add a bit of water or fruit juice to help it on its way. Keep the smoothie maker running until the ice has all broken up (no crackling).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pour out and enjoy.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
&lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/smoothiecast?a=tDjK1Qe1Qks:oUDGOvuZUIY:yIl2AUoC8zA"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/smoothiecast?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/smoothiecast?a=tDjK1Qe1Qks:oUDGOvuZUIY:UT3xtbGYFzA"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/smoothiecast?d=UT3xtbGYFzA" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/smoothiecast?a=tDjK1Qe1Qks:oUDGOvuZUIY:o5wlBzp-bFI"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/smoothiecast?d=o5wlBzp-bFI" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</description>
 <comments>http://www.smoothiecast.co.uk/smoothie+recipes/melon+apple+and+pear#comments</comments>
 <category domain="http://www.smoothiecast.co.uk/category/smoothie+recipes">Smoothie Recipes</category>
 <category domain="http://www.smoothiecast.co.uk/category/apple">Apple</category>
 <category domain="http://www.smoothiecast.co.uk/category/melon">Melon</category>
 <category domain="http://www.smoothiecast.co.uk/category/pear">Pear</category>
 <pubDate>Fri, 26 Jan 2007 05:42:36 -0800</pubDate>
 <dc:creator>mail@smoothiecast.co.uk (Ian Egner and Jake Mahal)</dc:creator>
 <guid isPermaLink="false">15 at http://www.smoothiecast.co.uk</guid>
<feedburner:origLink>http://www.smoothiecast.co.uk/smoothie+recipes/melon+apple+and+pear</feedburner:origLink></item>
<item>
 <title>Pineapple, Strawberry and Mango</title>
 <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/smoothiecast/~3/IgMlc75lvX8/pineapple+strawberry+and+mango</link>
 <description>&lt;p&gt;To make this super tasty smoothie you will need:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1 Medium mango&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10 Strawberries (frozen if possible)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;300ml Pineapple Juice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5 Ice Cubes (optional if strawberries are frozen)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Peel the Mango and slice off as much soft flesh as possible. Put the pieces in the smoothie maker. Before freezing the strawberries make sure you cut the tops off. If you haven't had time to freeze the strawberries don't worry, just add more ice. Put the ice in the smoothie maker then pur in the pineapple juice. Now you're ready to smooth, hit the on button and start smoothing. Let it run until the ingredients have smoothed, usually 30-40 seconds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pour out and enjoy!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
&lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/smoothiecast?a=IgMlc75lvX8:XuHpVv8-BLA:yIl2AUoC8zA"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/smoothiecast?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/smoothiecast?a=IgMlc75lvX8:XuHpVv8-BLA:UT3xtbGYFzA"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/smoothiecast?d=UT3xtbGYFzA" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/smoothiecast?a=IgMlc75lvX8:XuHpVv8-BLA:o5wlBzp-bFI"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/smoothiecast?d=o5wlBzp-bFI" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</description>
 <comments>http://www.smoothiecast.co.uk/smoothie+recipes/pineapple+strawberry+and+mango#comments</comments>
